# CodeRabbit CLI

Use CodeRabbit from the terminal to review changes. It is installed as `coderabbit` and `cr`; run `cr -h` (or `coderabbit -h`) for available commands.

## Default invocation

- Prefer the **`--agent`** flag so output suits an AI coding agent.
- For **uncommitted** changes (typical workflow):

```bash
coderabbit --agent -t uncommitted
```

Adjust targets (`-t`) when reviewing something other than the working tree, per `cr -h`.

## Frequency cap

**Do not run CodeRabbit more than three times for the same set of changes.** If a third run already happened, summarize or apply fixes without invoking the CLI again until the change set meaningfully updates.
